titles.short: Yes, but no thank you (Cuando sí, pero no)
titles.full: Yes, but no thank you (Cuando sí, pero no)

summaries.short: Six months after Juanito’s birth, María struggles with post-partum blues, and Gari sets out to get his driver’s license. Meanwhile, Cris and Pablo look to spice up their marriage, and Esther disappears into a new relationship.
summaries.full: Six months after Juanito’s birth, María struggles with post-partum blues, while Gari sets out to get his driver’s license. As Cris tries to ease her friend’s burden, she and Pablo consider spicing up their newly recommitted marriage. Later, at dinner with an absentee Esther and her new girlfriend Júlia, María is blindsided by unexpected news.

titles.short: When you try to start over again (Cuando intentas volver a empezar)
titles.full: When you try to start over again (Cuando intentas volver a empezar)

summaries.short: At therapy, María finally digs into her true feelings towards motherhood. Cris and Pablo navigate the reality of open boundaries, Esther and Julia’s visions for the future start to clash, and later, María reconnects with Xosé.
summaries.full: At therapy, an initially skeptical María laments feeling trapped in an unfulfilling life while everyone around her seems to be moving forward with theirs. As Cris and Pablo navigate the reality of open boundaries, Esther and Júlia’s visions for the future start to clash. Later, María reconnects with Xosé, while Cris bumps into a familiar stranger.

titles.full: When you let yourself go (Cuando te dejas llevar)

summaries.short: María’s wedding day is full of surprises that give her, Esther, and Cris some overdue clarity on what they want out of life.
summaries.full: After her wedding leaves Gari feeling insecure, María goes into labor while trying to reassure him. At the hospital, she finally gets some overdue clarity on what she really wants out of life. Meanwhile, Cris and Esther have some transformative realizations of their own.

titles.short: When you want what you can't have (Cuando quieres lo que no tienes)
titles.full: When you want what you can't have (Cuando quieres lo que no tienes)

summaries.short: Esther takes a job to avoid Júlia – and her wedding doubts. Gari struggles with the outcome of his driver’s test and ill-timed news of María and Xosé’s rekindled flame. Cris breaches her agreement with Pablo.
summaries.full: After a distressing visit to their wedding venue, Esther takes a job to avoid Júlia, while Gari fixates on the outcome of his driver’s test… and news of María and Xosé’s rekindled flame. As Cris begins to bend the rules of the sex contract, Pablo grows increasingly wary of their arrangement.

summaries.short: El final. But is it? Dany and Ada discuss the age old Latinx adage, "Querer es Poder" and its potential damage.
summaries.full: El final. But is it? Dany and Ada discuss the age old Latinx adage, "Querer es Poder" and its potential damage, Maria's mom confessing her affair, and Gari turning the tables on Maria while she gives birth. Un poco de todo and it's a wrap - or shall we say mantilla?

titles.full: When everything falls apart (Cuando todo se derrumba)

summaries.short: While Esther hits rock bottom on her 40th birthday, María tries to get Gari comfortable with Gustavo, and Cris lets her guard down at home.
summaries.full: On Esther’s 40th birthday, a series of stressful encounters make it clear that she’s lost control of her life, prompting her to go rogue. Meanwhile, María arranges for Gari and Gustavo to get to know each other, and Cris’ string of affairs finally catches up to her.

titles.short: When it all goes way back (Cuando todo viene de lejos)
titles.full: When it all goes way back (Cuando todo viene de lejos)

summaries.short: While Esther remains apprehensive about their impending nuptials, Júlia immerses herself in her fiancé’s world. As he grows closer to María and Juanito, Xosé gets cold feet. Cris ignores Pablo’s plea for monogamy.
summaries.full: As he becomes more involved in María and Juanito’s lives, Xosé’s deep-seated feelings towards parenthood bubble to the service. Despite being in a monogamous marriage once again, Cris further explores her connection with Álex. While Esther continues to hide her apprehension about their impending nuptials, Júlia attempts to immerse herself in her fiancé’s world.

summaries.short: Ada and Dany welcome back "Dr. Adri" from Latinx Therapy and discuss self-sabotaging behavior (:ahem: Esther).
summaries.full: Ada and Dany welcome back "Dr. Adri" from Latinx Therapy and discuss self-sabotaging behavior (:ahem: Esther), how the grass is not always greener on the other side and how both Cristina and Gari call it like it is. Cristina cutting someone else's grass notwithstanding. ¡Ay!

summaries.short: At their 15-year high school reunion, María and Cris contemplate how far they’ve strayed from the lives they once envisioned for themselves.
summaries.full: As their 15-year high school reunion approaches, María braves prenatal classes and gynecology appointments with Gari, while, thanks to Pablo, Cris finds herself increasingly torn between work and mom duties. At the reunion, they contemplate how far they’ve strayed from the lives they once envisioned for themselves.
